casebody.data:
Amy v. Manning, Appellant. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. July 9, 1889.) Appeal from special term, New York county.

Argued before Van Brunt, P. J., and Brady and Daniels, JJ.

Philip Carpenter, for appellant. William J. Weldon, pro se. Van Brunt, P. J.

The opinion in the case of Tuck v. Manning, ante, 140, disposes of the appeal in this ease. The order must be reversed, and an. order of substitution granted, without costs. All concur.
